town officials say they cant afford 
3000 worth of tests to pinpoint the site of a 211yearold jail 
the first prison authorized by the continental congress 
the town is in a financial dilemma town clerk irene amsden 
said tuesday this is not the time to be asking for money for 
such a project 
during the revolutionary war the jail housed 3000 british and 
german prisoners 
the prison was abandoned in 1783 and eventually turned over to 
private hands in 1828 part of it burned the rest later was torn 
down 
two boston university archaeology students want to make sonar 
tests and aerial surveys to pinpoint the jails foundation the 
state historical commission pledged 3000 toward the tests if the 
central massachusetts town of 1400 people comes up with another 
3000 
