<TEXT>
a strong earthquake jolted the indonesian 
island of java this morning the hong kong royal observatory 
reported there were no immediate reports of damage or injury 
the 1005 am 1005 pm edt tuesday earthquake with an 
estimated 53 magnitude on the richter scale was centered about 
140 miles southeast of jakarta the observatory reported 
the richter scale gauges energy released by an earthquake as 
measured by the ground motion recorded on a seismograph every 
increase of one number means the ground motion is 10 times greater 
a quake of magnitude 5 can cause considerable damage in 
populated areas a quake of magnitude 6 can cause severe damage 
</TEXT>
