tonight he said 
where else could we be today asked betty polec of mount 
clemens whose daughter and soninlaw died in the aug 16 1987 
crash the nations secondworst air disaster she cofounded a 
support group for the victims relatives 
relatives friends and a few people unknown to the victims stood 
next to 156 plastic foam hearts arranged to form the numeral 255 
each bore an artificial rose and a ribbon with a victims name 
flowers were laid at some of them 
aircraft roared overhead as lund pointed out a wispy pink cloud 
in the shape of a dove the symbol adopted by the support group 
in the darkening sky 
if you dont believe in miracles look and see the dove in 
the air he said 
at 746 pm the hour and minute of the crash the names of 
the victims were read as each name was called out tiny penlights 
were turned on and held up until they formed 255 in the 
gathering darkness 
the phoenixbound md80 aircraft broke apart in flames less than 
a minute after takeoff from metropolitan airport two people on the 
ground and all but one of the 155 people aboard the plane died 
the only survivor was cecelia cichan 4 of tempe ariz whose 
parents and brother died in the crash no cichan family members 
were present tuesday they were represented by two employees at the 
university of michigan medical center where cecelia spent 68 days 
recovering 
cecelia is living with an aunt and uncle in birmingham ala 
im sure their thoughts are going to be with everyone here 
said catherine cureton a hospital spokeswoman 
also on hand was allison maus of las vegas nev the widow of 
the planes pilot john maus 
although investigators linked the crash to pilot error mrs 
maus said she has been comforted by relatives of the passengers 
there was never any peace to be made they all realize my 
husband was killed just like their family and friends and i 
consider them my very dear friends she said 
the national transportation safety board issued a finding may 10 
that flight 255s two pilots failed to set the airplanes flaps 
properly 
attorneys have filed 106 lawsuits over the crash and 10 
settlements have been reached 
