<TEXT>
rain poured down on the capital today and 
the nile rose higher as the city tried to cope with the worst 
flooding in its history 
news reports today said an additional 21 people died in 
accidents caused by the floods bringing the total known death toll 
to more than 90 
torrential rains aug 45 left 15 million to 2 million people 
homeless as thousands of mud huts melted in the refugee camps that 
ring this desert city 
in khartoum alone 70 people died 213 were injured and nearly 
115000 houses were destroyed by the flooding egypts stateowned 
middle east news agency quoted amin abdellatif sudans ambassador 
to cairo as saying tuesday 
the agency said today that 18 sudanese drowned when their ferry 
overturned in fast currents on the rahad river the river is a 
tributary of the blue nile which joins the white nile at khartoum 
to form the nile river 
in omdurman across the nile from khartoum the agency said 
