25 of gaza city and bassam ibrahim al samoudi 27 of yamoun 
village in the west bank both were serving sixmonth terms without 
trial under administrative detention 
the yediot ahronot daily said the riot began during a visit by 
representatives of the international red cross the organization 
could not immediately be reached for comment 
other reports said it began after news of violence and of the 
curfew in gaza where many inmates live 
about 1000 prisoners in one section of the prison shouted 
palestinian nationalist slogans cursed and hurled rocks at 
soldiers and tried to scale a barbedwire fence the haaretz 
newspaper said 
soldiers reportedly responded by firing tear gas rubber bullets 
and then live ammunition at the rioters 
