we in our own generation are becoming afraid of the sun and air 
these givers of life that sustain and nourish us have been turned 
by years of humanitys greed ignorance and indifference into alien 
elements 
suddenly we are more aware than ever of living in a damaged 
cocoon 
daily reports on the greenhouse effect and the ozone drive us 
from our natural environment in search of artificial shelter 
the daily weather report jars us as we check the air quality and 
pollution standard index we read and find what new horror from 
drought and heat awaits this delicate sphere and its inhabitants 
 
pollutants from rivers cleaners and pesticides are taking a 
destructive toll on the fragile body of water that hugs our shores 
the fish dont have oxygen careless dumping is poisoning the 
waterfront 
we are killing the water the very place where life on the 
planet began 
time is running out we must arise awaken and save our earth 
