mohammed zia ulhaq who seized power 
in military coup 11 years ago and became pakistans longest serving 
president ruled with an iron hand that bore the stamp of islam 
zia a strong us ally died today when his military plane 
exploded just after taking off from bahawalpur 330 miles southwest 
of islamabad he was 64 
the career military officer strongly supported afghan guerrillas 
in their struggle against the sovietbacked marxist government of 
afghanistan recently the soviets told him to stop allowing arms 
for the rebels to pass through pakistan while the soviets withdraw 
their troops 
zia kept up his nations military strength to guard tense 
borders with neighboring india he managed to retain control over 
the armed forces which had staged several successful coups since 
pakistan was created as an islamic nation in 1947 
but in recent months he has faced increasingly unified 
opposition led by benazir bhutto the daughter of former prime 
minister zulfikar ali bhutto who zia arrested and executed after 
taking power 
zia who was a general resisted a cult of personality and did 
not permit his portrait to hang in government offices or public 
places unlike pakistans previous military leaders he was married 
and had five children 
he was also the countrys first head of state to use pakistans 
national language urdu at all state functions he also encouraged 
officials in his government to wear national dress 
zia took power from bhutto in 1977 arrested the cabinet and 
proclaimed martial law two years later he ordered his predecessor 
executed on charges of conspiracy to murder under his 
authoritarian rule mass arrests and floggings were frequent 
in an interview earlier this month zia said he ruled 
reluctantly 
really you can say that a reluctant ruler but i am not a 
person to just give up in disgust and walk away i am determined to 
stay here until i solve all of the many problems that continue to 
face our country 
he was born into a middleclass family on aug 12 1924 at 
jallunder in what is now indias punjab state he became a devout 
moslem in his youth and later instituted islamic laws when in 
power 
in june zia issued a presidential decree making islamic law 
supreme bringing much of pakistani life under the supervision of 
islamic scholars and priests his great passion in life is 
islam said a close aide 
his rule was helped by geopolitics and luck the soviet 
intervention in afghanistan in 1979 led to more western aid and 
good harvests brought more food in the early 1980s 
in recent months however he has had to work a political high 
wire act to quell the unprecedented opposition challenge by ms 
bhutto and others 
last month zia announced free fair and impartial national 
elections would be held in november but he later issued election 
rules that restricted opposition campaigning 
several pakistani and western analysts said the shrewd leader 
had believed that running the country was not duty but destiny 
its not important what people say about you now zia said 
in a 1983 interview but what history remembers after youve 
gone 
