<TEXT>
here are some facts and figures on pakistan 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the land pakistan covers 310403 square miles about twice the 
size of california the southern asian country considered 
strategically important to the united states borders india china 
afghanistan and iran it also has a coastline on the arabian sea 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the people pakistans 102 million people come from three main 
ethnic groups punjabis the most numerous and the pathans in the 
northwest and baluchis in the west urdu is the official language 
although english is widely used about 98 percent of the population 
are moslems and a presidential decree in june brought much of 
pakistani life under the supervision of islamic scholars and 
priests 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the economy agriculture dominates pakistans economy and 
principal crops are wheat rice cotton and sugarcane the nation 
exports texiles and produces chemicals steel natural gas and 
cement there is some mining for iron ore 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
history aryans persians greeks arabs and turks conquered 
the region before it became part of british india in 1857 in 1947 
the colony was divided into the hindudominated nation of india and 
the islamic republic of pakistan one of pakistans two parts east 
pakistan became the separate country of bangladesh in 1971 
pakistan stations tens of thousands of troops alongside its 
tense 1836mile border with india site of three wars in the past 
41 years a un observer force has manned a stretch of the border 
in the disputed kashmirjammu region since 1949 
on july 5 1977 gen mohammed zia ulhaq took power from prime 
minister ali bhutto the army commander arrested bhutto and ordered 
his execution in 1979 zia imposed martial law until 1985 when he 
restored basic rights and appointed a civilian cabinet in may he 
fired the civilian government saying it had failed to maintain law 
and order and to enact islamic law two months later he announced 
general elections would be held in november 
