more convenience stores record shops supermarkets and bookstores 
are now stocking cassettes according to a survey of the booming 
business released at the recent software dealers meeting in las 
vegas 
last year and this year business has been real good said 
association spokesman ray gianchetti sixtysix percent of the 
video merchants surveyed by the group said business went up from 
1985 to 1987 according to the poll released at last weeks 
convention 
tape rental prices averaged 245 per tape in 1987 video stores 
stock an average of 2832 titles and the number of videos rented 
per visit was 23 the survey revealed while most video time is 
spent viewing prerecorded tapes some folks use their vcrs to 
record programs for later viewing 
of the seven hours of an average week when the vcr is in use 24 
hours are spent recording programs and 47 hours viewing tapes agb 
reported last march twentythree percent of the time is used 
taping shows for later viewing known as timeshifting 
homes with pay cable channels spent more time recording and less 
time playing tapes than those without cable the study found most 
taping is during evening primetime hours or during weekdays and 
most viewing is during weekend days late nights and early 
mornings 
