the us trade deficit widened to 125 
billion in june as imports hit an alltime high according to a 
government report that analysts said shows how far the country 
still has to go to solve its trade problems 
the gap between what america exports and what the country 
imports surged by 285 percent in june a major setback after three 
consecutive monthly improvements the commerce department said 
tuesday 
for the first six months of the year the deficit was running at 
an annual rate of 140 billion down from the record 1703 billion 
deficit set in 1987 
</TEXT>
