<TEXT>
share prices were mixed in lackluster trading at 
midday wednesday with the markets nearterm outlook clouded by 
concerns about britains economy 
the financial timesstock exchange 100share index was up 29 
points or 02 percent at 18282 at about 1230 pm 
among the top 100 shares 37 were higher 34 were lower and 29 
were unchanged 
volume was thin with 1713 million shares changing hands by 
midday compared with 1688 million shares at the same time tuesday 
most shares languished in morning dealings with activity 
concentrated on a few selected shares 
underlying the markets reticence to trade are concerns about 
possible overheating in the british economy highlighted by a 
report by the organization of economic cooperation and development 
the report warned of renewed inflationary pressures in the 
british economy 
